-♪ I want my baby back. baby back ♪
-♪ Chili's baby back ribs ♪

484
00:21:32.041 --> 00:21:35.958
-♪ Chili's baby back ribs ♪
-♪ Chili's baby back ribs ♪

485
00:21:36.041 --> 00:21:38.625
-♪ Chili's baby back ribs ♪
-♪ Chili's baby back ribs ♪

486
00:21:38.708 --> 00:21:41.041
-♪ Barbecue sauce ♪
-♪ Barbecue sauce ♪

487
00:21:41.125 --> 00:21:43.958
-[laughing]
-Sam! You sly dog!

488
00:21:44.041 --> 00:21:47.041
You got me singing on national television
in front of the whole world!

489
00:21:47.125 --> 00:21:49.583
Good! Show 'em how it's done.

490
00:21:50.291 --> 00:21:52.291
[stirring music builds slowly]

491
00:21:57.291 --> 00:21:58.208
-[rocks slide]
-Oh!

492
00:21:58.291 --> 00:21:59.875
-Holy… shit.
-Watch it. You good?

493
00:21:59.958 --> 00:22:01.250
-Yeah. I'm good.
-All right.

494
00:22:01.333 --> 00:22:02.416
All right. be careful.

495
00:22:05.500 --> 00:22:06.666
[sighs]

496
00:22:10.541 --> 00:22:11.583
[huffs]

497
00:22:12.416 --> 00:22:13.458
[exhales]

498
00:22:14.958 --> 00:22:16.958
[majestic music rises]

499
00:22:21.208 --> 00:22:22.291
[grunts]

500
00:22:22.375 --> 00:22:23.541
[groaning] Ah!

501
00:22:37.041 --> 00:22:38.375
[cheers and applause]

502
00:22:42.416 --> 00:22:43.875
[laughing quietly]

503
00:22:43.958 --> 00:22:45.458
Whoo-hoo! Yes!

504
00:22:45.541 --> 00:22:47.500
-No fucking way.
-[Lonnie] Yeah!

505
00:22:47.583 --> 00:22:52.250
We have just witnessed
the greatest shot in golf history.

506
00:22:52.333 --> 00:22:54.583
How in the world did he pull that off?

507
00:22:57.625 --> 00:22:59.625
Excuse me. please. Excuse me.

508
00:22:59.708 --> 00:23:03.000
Sam. I'm gonna need
a new MacGregor two-iron.

509
00:23:03.583 --> 00:23:06.250
And call me a vet to reset my hand.

510
00:23:06.333 --> 00:23:08.541
All right. you got it.

511
00:23:08.625 --> 00:23:10.166
[laughing] Yeah!

512
00:23:11.458 --> 00:23:12.916
Heck of a shot. Lonnie!

513
00:23:13.000 --> 00:23:14.041
Yeah. it was!

514
00:23:14.125 --> 00:23:16.333
It was a heck of a shot. Golden!

515
00:23:16.416 --> 00:23:18.333
Hey. give this to someone you love!

516
00:23:18.416 --> 00:23:20.500
Hell of a souvenir!

517
00:23:20.583 --> 00:23:22.958
[overlapping shouts]

518
00:23:23.041 --> 00:23:25.041
[funky up-tempo music playing]

519
00:23:30.500 --> 00:23:31.791
Keep it close.

520
00:23:32.375 --> 00:23:35.250
[Dan] As if the afternoon
needed any more drama.

521
00:23:35.333 --> 00:23:38.875
the fog has once again decided
to roll in here at Pebble Beach.

522
00:23:39.791 --> 00:23:43.166
We'll just have to wait and see
how this affects our finalists

523
00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:45.333
as they all head to the 18th green.

524
00:23:45.416 --> 00:23:46.250
[music fades]

525
00:23:46.333 --> 00:23:48.333
[bluesy harmonica playing]

526
00:23:57.916 --> 00:23:59.333
Front right quadrant.

527
00:24:00.250 --> 00:24:01.791
Front left quadrant.

528
00:24:02.791 --> 00:24:04.208
Back right and left.

529
00:24:05.083 --> 00:24:06.083
Gentlemen…

530
00:24:06.166 --> 00:24:07.166
[sighs]

531
00:24:07.750 --> 00:24:11.541
I can do this all day long.
I will wear you down eventually.

532
00:24:11.625 --> 00:24:13.333
Golden. you're about to fuck this up.

533
00:24:13.416 --> 00:24:14.458
[Golden chuckles]

534
00:24:20.583 --> 00:24:22.291
[crowd groans]

535
00:24:22.375 --> 00:24:23.250
[fart noise]

536
00:24:23.333 --> 00:24:26.041
[Dan] Oh. a devastating miss
for Fisk here.

537
00:24:26.125 --> 00:24:27.000
[sad note]

538
00:24:27.083 --> 00:24:31.041
[Dan] And that just about
closes the door on any hopes for a win.

539
00:24:31.125 --> 00:24:32.208
[cheers and applause]

540
00:24:35.666 --> 00:24:37.208
Oopsie-daisy.

541
00:24:37.291 --> 00:24:38.916
[Lance] Tough break. Golden.

542
00:24:41.375 --> 00:24:42.375
Well. Dad…

543
00:24:43.791 --> 00:24:45.166
Whatever happens.

544
00:24:46.625 --> 00:24:47.875
I love you.

545
00:24:48.791 --> 00:24:50.916
Just want you to know that. in case…

546
00:24:52.666 --> 00:24:53.708
Well…

547
00:24:54.458 --> 00:24:55.666
Never mind.

548
00:24:55.750 --> 00:24:57.750
[somber music playing]

549
00:25:08.916 --> 00:25:10.708
[exhales heavily]

550
00:25:19.083 --> 00:25:20.166
[chuckles softly]

551
00:25:24.791 --> 00:25:26.791
-[indistinct whispering]
-[exhales]

552
00:25:27.333 --> 00:25:29.333
[solemn music builds slowly]

553
00:25:40.875 --> 00:25:42.291
Yay!

554
00:25:42.375 --> 00:25:47.000
[Dan] With that putt. Lance Hawkins
continues to put pressure on his father.

555
00:25:47.625 --> 00:25:51.708
Lonnie will have to make his putt
in order to stay in this playoff.

556
00:25:51.791 --> 00:25:53.416
to continue here at Pebble Beach.

557
00:25:53.500 --> 00:25:56.833
and to maintain his chances
for that Grand Slam.

558
00:25:57.625 --> 00:26:00.333
If he misses. it's all over.

559
00:26:00.416 --> 00:26:05.458
Lance Hawkins will be the winner
of this 126th US Open.

560
00:26:32.041 --> 00:26:34.083
Son. I'm gonna have to make this putt.

561
00:26:35.166 --> 00:26:36.666
Do what you got to do.

562
00:26:37.166 --> 00:26:39.583
Lonnie Hawkins has been here before.

563
00:26:40.250 --> 00:26:42.750
What could he be thinking?

564
00:26:44.958 --> 00:26:46.458
[Lonnie] Hey. Lance!

565
00:26:49.083 --> 00:26:50.083
Lance.

566
00:26:51.708 --> 00:26:53.125
[Lance] Hey. Dad.

567
00:26:53.791 --> 00:26:54.875
[Lonnie] Hey. Lance.

568
00:26:55.458 --> 00:26:58.750
Would it be okay if I… made that putt?

569
00:26:59.750 --> 00:27:03.125
[Lance] I'd be the proudest son
in the world if you made that putt.

570
00:27:03.708 --> 00:27:04.958
[Lonnie] I love you. son.

571
00:27:05.750 --> 00:27:07.708
[Lance] I love you too. Dad.

572
00:27:09.541 --> 00:27:11.666
[rapid gunfire]

573
00:27:14.500 --> 00:27:16.833
[haunting music plays]

574
00:27:24.041 --> 00:27:26.041
-[gasps. panting]
-[music fades out]

575
00:27:29.583 --> 00:27:31.333
[melancholy music playing slowly]

576
00:27:51.083 --> 00:27:53.541
[Lonnie] Sorry. son.
I got to make this putt.

577
00:27:53.625 --> 00:27:55.833
[Lance] Do what you got to do. Dad.

578
00:28:00.958 --> 00:28:02.791
-[exhales]
-[tense notes rise slowly]

579
00:28:11.250 --> 00:28:13.791
-[crowd groans softly]
-[disenchanting notes play]

580
00:28:15.916 --> 00:28:16.750
Yes!

581
00:28:16.833 --> 00:28:18.833
Welcome to the club. kid.

582
00:28:18.916 --> 00:28:20.625
Let's go!

583
00:28:20.708 --> 00:28:22.583
[majestic music plays]

584
00:28:22.666 --> 00:28:23.875
[Lance] Whoo!

585
00:28:26.916 --> 00:28:28.125
Whoo!

586
00:28:28.708 --> 00:28:29.708
Wonderful!

587
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:31.583
I missed that on purpose.

588
00:28:33.666 --> 00:28:34.916
I missed it on purpose.

589
00:28:35.500 --> 00:28:37.458
Dad. Great game.

590
00:28:39.416 --> 00:28:40.666
I missed on purpose. son.

591
00:28:43.083 --> 00:28:44.083
Well. I lied.

592
00:28:44.750 --> 00:28:46.458
No one wanted to kill me.

593
00:28:47.041 --> 00:28:48.041
Huh?

594
00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:50.333
What?

595
00:28:50.416 --> 00:28:52.208
Thanks for the tickets. Lance!

596
00:28:54.583 --> 00:28:56.416
It's a mental game. Dad.

597
00:28:56.500 --> 00:28:58.125
You taught me that.

598
00:28:58.208 --> 00:29:00.041
I had to get in your head somehow.

599
00:29:02.041 --> 00:29:03.208
You lied?

600
00:29:03.291 --> 00:29:04.583
[chuckles quietly]

601
00:29:04.666 --> 00:29:06.000
You beat me at my own game.

602
00:29:06.083 --> 00:29:07.375
Yeah. [laughing]

603
00:29:07.458 --> 00:29:09.291
You beat me at my own game!

604
00:29:09.375 --> 00:29:12.166
-I got... [laughs]
-[laughing] You beat me at my own game!

605
00:29:12.250 --> 00:29:14.875
[majestic music swells]

606
00:29:14.958 --> 00:29:17.166
Oh my God. you son of a…

607
00:29:17.250 --> 00:29:18.250
[Lance laughs]

608
00:29:18.291 --> 00:29:21.500
Oh. Radford. I'm so sorry.
I cannot marry you.

609
00:29:22.041 --> 00:29:24.833
Because I am in love with that man.

610
00:29:25.416 --> 00:29:28.916
My son. Lance Hawkins. US Open champion!

611
00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:31.000
[cheers and applause]

612
00:29:31.083 --> 00:29:32.500
-[huffs]
-[music turns grim]

613
00:29:34.375 --> 00:29:35.375
[gasps]

614
00:29:36.041 --> 00:29:36.875
[growls]

615
00:29:36.958 --> 00:29:39.250
Go to hell. Lonnie Hawkins!

616
00:29:39.333 --> 00:29:40.708
[grunts]

617
00:29:41.833 --> 00:29:43.875
[discordant music playing slowly]

618
00:29:46.166 --> 00:29:48.291
[slowed] Oh shit.

619
00:29:50.375 --> 00:29:51.916
-[pings]
-[music halts]

620
00:29:52.666 --> 00:29:56.000
-[classic rock music plays]
-[Dan] That is a perfect javelin throw.

621
00:29:56.083 --> 00:29:58.833
Beautiful form.
And by the way. nice snag by the caddie.

622
00:29:58.916 --> 00:30:00.250
-[screams]
-[grunting]

623
00:30:00.333 --> 00:30:01.958
[groans] Honeybunch!

624
00:30:02.041 --> 00:30:04.375
-[majestic music rises]
-[cheers and applause]

625
00:30:04.458 --> 00:30:05.625
[laughing]

626
00:30:05.708 --> 00:30:08.708
[laughing] Oh my God!
Look! I can't believe I caught this.

627
00:30:08.791 --> 00:30:10.833
[laughing maniacally]

628
00:30:10.916 --> 00:30:14.000
I fucking love golf. Sport of kings.

629
00:30:14.750 --> 00:30:16.750
Sam. that was a hell of a catch!

630
00:30:16.833 --> 00:30:18.000
[chuckles]

631
00:30:18.750 --> 00:30:20.250
You saved my life.

632
00:30:21.208 --> 00:30:22.916
That's what caddies do.

633
00:30:23.666 --> 00:30:24.875
[sighs]

634
00:30:27.750 --> 00:30:28.833
-Yeah!
-Oh my God!

635
00:30:28.916 --> 00:30:30.208
-Whoo!
-[cackling]

636
00:30:30.291 --> 00:30:32.791
Oh. I love you so much.
I'm so proud of you.

637
00:30:32.875 --> 00:30:36.083
If that was a 40-yard dash.
your time would be under two seconds.

638
00:30:36.166 --> 00:30:39.375
-God dang.
-You should go to the NFL Combines.

639
00:30:39.458 --> 00:30:41.583
Yeah. I'm fucking amazing.

640
00:30:41.666 --> 00:30:43.458
God dang it. Look at you.

641
00:30:43.541 --> 00:30:45.458
-Look at me!
-You never cease to amaze!

642
00:30:45.541 --> 00:30:46.958
[Sam laughs] Dude!

643
00:30:47.041 --> 00:30:48.416
That was crazy.

644
00:30:48.500 --> 00:30:49.750
[music fades]

645
00:30:52.166 --> 00:30:54.625
[chill music playing]

646
00:31:01.208 --> 00:31:03.041
Here's what I don't understand.

647
00:31:03.125 --> 00:31:05.125
Why is your stupid hand back in that cast?

648
00:31:05.208 --> 00:31:08.166
Well. I had to reset it.
and then it wasn't healing right...

649
00:31:08.250 --> 00:31:12.166
And it got infected. so then I had to
reset it from the first time I reset it.

650
00:31:12.250 --> 00:31:16.000
And then I got gangrene
and started oozing discharge and…

651
00:31:16.083 --> 00:31:17.875
I mean. at one point.

652
00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:20.541
there was spider eggs coming out of it.

653
00:31:20.625 --> 00:31:22.208
It was like Charlotte's Web.

654
00:31:22.291 --> 00:31:24.541
Then I looked up a hand surgeon.

655
00:31:24.625 --> 00:31:28.041
He wanted to chop the thing off.
I fought for it. I fought like hell.

656
00:31:28.541 --> 00:31:30.000
Reset it. and here we are.

657
00:31:30.083 --> 00:31:33.958
[reporter] Lance. how does it feel to win
the US Open and beat your own father?

658
00:31:34.041 --> 00:31:37.000
Ugh… Honestly? Complicated.

659
00:31:37.083 --> 00:31:39.666
I mean. I wish we both could've won. but…

660
00:31:40.541 --> 00:31:42.666
You know. I did.

661
00:31:42.750 --> 00:31:46.250
Do you think you'll take some time
to rest and enjoy this historic win?

662
00:31:46.833 --> 00:31:51.041
Actually. we're doing a cross-country
road trip together while he recovers.

663
00:31:51.125 --> 00:31:54.708
Yeah. we're gonna go to the
Carlsbad Caverns. the NASA Space Museum…

664
00:31:54.791 --> 00:31:56.375
Think you'll be able to golf again?

665
00:31:56.458 --> 00:32:00.500
Believe it or not. they asked me to be
the captain of the Ryder Cup next year.

666
00:32:00.583 --> 00:32:01.583
-What?
-Yeah!

667
00:32:01.666 --> 00:32:02.541
Oh my God!

668
00:32:02.625 --> 00:32:06.000
Not gonna keep this apex predator
off the golf course. You know that.

669
00:32:06.083 --> 00:32:07.416
That's right.

670
00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:11.500
Not all the bumps and bruises
and boulders and bullshit.

671
00:32:11.583 --> 00:32:14.208
-Delicious beats bullshit.
-Beats bullshit. That's right.

672
00:32:14.291 --> 00:32:15.875
-Every time.
-Every time.

673
00:32:15.958 --> 00:32:17.541
[Lance] You know. in many ways.

674
00:32:17.625 --> 00:32:20.083
this experience has
brought us closer together.

675
00:32:20.166 --> 00:32:24.166
You know. we've just… we've realized.
you know. how much we have in common.

676
00:32:24.250 --> 00:32:26.500
Four cartons of fucking milk?

677
00:32:26.583 --> 00:32:28.500
Bad. Bad. Bad…

678
00:32:28.583 --> 00:32:32.041
I mean. cheese balls. wine. Triscuits?
I can't fucking live like this.

679
00:32:32.125 --> 00:32:33.583
[reporter] Sorry. I missed that.

680
00:32:33.666 --> 00:32:36.833
Oh. yeah. I said. at the end of the day.

681
00:32:36.916 --> 00:32:40.083
it's just great to know
how much we have each other's backs.

682
00:32:41.625 --> 00:32:45.000
Well. I'm sorry that you lost
the US Open. Lonnie.

683
00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:46.833
That's some bullshit.

684
00:32:46.916 --> 00:32:48.125
Yeah.

685
00:32:49.458 --> 00:32:51.333
That would have been something else.

686
00:32:51.416 --> 00:32:52.416
[Sam] Mm-hmm.

687
00:32:52.458 --> 00:32:54.250
[music fades]

688
00:32:54.333 --> 00:32:57.125
You did the right thing. though.
missing that putt.

689
00:33:02.083 --> 00:33:04.166
You did miss it on purpose. right?

